The paper deals with video surveillance and human tracking, which are common topics in computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO). The use of wearable cameras and drone-mounted cameras also suggests a potential connection to multimedia (cs.MM). The proposed approach involves modeling and matching subjects' spatial distributions, which could involve machine learning techniques (cs.AI) and optimization algorithms (cs.LG).
